      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "cumin seeds",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "coriander powder",
      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add onion and garlic, sauté for about 3 minutes until fragrant but not browned.",
    "Stir in ginger paste and tomato paste, cook for another minute until paste is slightly thickened.",
    "Pour in vegetable broth, lemon juice, salt, turmeric powder, cumin seeds, and coriander powder. Bring to a simmer.",
    "Gently fold in the chopped pistachios. Let them cook for 2-3 minutes until heated through and slightly golden.",
    "Serve hot with crusty bread."
  ],
